5	Contact Us	<p>Contact us:&nbsp;<span style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.85); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;"><a href="mailto:contact@ou.com">contact@ou.com</a></span></p>	contact-us
2	Enterprise Customers	<p style="margin-bottom: 1em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.85); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;">ou has four offerings for enterprise customers:</p><ol style="margin-bottom: 1em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.85); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;"><li><span style="font-weight: bolder;">Company Channel</span>&nbsp;- a private area on ou.com for your company. Your private products and tasks are only visible and available to your selected contributors.</li><li><span style="font-weight: bolder;">Paid Tasks</span>&nbsp;- contributors earn a payment for completing tasks on your oopen products that are posted publicly.</li><li><span style="font-weight: bolder;">Private Instance</span>&nbsp;- your own self-managed instance of the ou platform. This can be hosted on a cloud provider of your choice (e.g. AWS, Azure, GCP, Digital Ocean) and is completely separate from ou.com. For example product-factory.yourcomapny.com</li><li><span style="font-weight: bolder;">Professional Services</span>&nbsp;- if your company needs help with Product Management (e.g. creating ProductMaps), Business Analysis or in using the ou platform, we have specialists available to help starting at just $70 per hour.</li></ol><p style="margin-bottom: 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.85); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;">If you are interested in any of these offerings, please email <a href="mailto:contact@ou.com">contact@ou.com</a></p>	enterprise-customers
1	About Us	<h1>About ou</h1>\r\n<h2>Connecting creators everywhere</h2>\r\n<div class="pt-15 mb-20">\r\n<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/OWXVryhdoVA" title="YouTube video player" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="" width="450" height="300" frameborder="0"></iframe>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>What is ou?</strong></p>\r\n<p>ou is the place where communities - comprising contributors of all kinds - come together to create and contribute to Open Products.</p>\r\n<p>The software platform that powers ou.com is itself an open product - it’s just one of the open products that you can contribute to with your skills.</p>\r\n<p>ou is underpinned by a simple yet powerful product management framework that greatly reduces the time required to understand what products do, and how your skills can help.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What's in it for me?</strong></p>\r\n<p>As you contribute your skills to open products at ou, you are building up a portfolio of your work - a rich portfolio where everyone can see your work and skills in action - because your work is on open products and therefore visible publicly. Your ou portfolio can help you realise the next step in your career, to avoid frustrating fake assignments in job interviews and even to potentially earn a share of new companies that are created around the Open Products that you have contributed to.</p>\r\n<p>The software platform that powers <a href="https://ou.com" target="_blank">ou.com</a> is itself an open product - it’s just one of the open products that you can contribute to with your skills. We plan to make "phantom shares" in ou available to contributors that make signficant contributions over an extended period of time. These phantom shares will convert into a total of 5% of the future ou company available to selected contributors. If you help make ou great, you can earn a share of what we believe is set to be a "Unicorn".</p>\r\n<p><strong>Why is ou needed?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Despite open source software being hugely successful over past decades, there have been no common ways of explaining what products do, nor the work to be done - often because open source projects are not products. They are projects that do not have a strong product management discipline, and in many cases they do not have a roadmap, they lack clearly defined goals, documentation and the work to be done is also unclear.</p>\r\n<p>Graphic Designers, Product Managers, Business Analysts, Finance Experts, Lawyers and others with super valuable skills, don’t write source code - so even the name “open source” suggests there are barriers to them contributing. The problems are much bigger than naming however - the terminology, practices, platforms and tools that open source projects use - such as git and Github -  are deeply technical and designed for developers only. Ever heard of a graphic designer doing a “git pull request”?</p>\r\n<p>For many people who can code, becoming a contributor is also intimidating - often there isn’t an efficient or effective way of figuring out where to start, finding specific work to contribute or even how to interact with other contributors on that project.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Who are the founders and investors?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Adrian McPhee  <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/adrianmcphee/" class="ml-5" target="_blank"><img src="https://ou.com/images/attachments/2021-04-22%2012:12:30%20bf0c58ed.png" alt="linkedin" style="width: 20px"></a> <a href="https://twitter.com/adrianmcphee" target="_blank" class="ml-5"><img src="https://o-u.herokuapp.com/images/attachments/2021-04-22%2012:11:25%208cf00bdc.png" alt="twitter" style="width: 20px;"></a></p>\r\n<p>Farbod Saraf <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/farbodsaraf/" class="ml-5" target="_blank"><img src="https://ou.com/images/attachments/2021-04-22%2012:12:30%20bf0c58ed.png" alt="linkedin" style="width: 20px"></a> <a href="https://twitter.com/farbodsaraf" target="_blank" class="ml-5"><img src="https://ou.com/images/attachments/2021-04-22%2012:11:25%208cf00bdc.png" alt="twitter" style="width: 20px;"></a></p>\r\n<p>To date, we have designed/built and funded ou ourselves. We are now using the product to manage itself and we need your help to make ou a success. Please find a task that matches your skills, claim it and get started!</p>\r\n<p>As above, we plan to make "phantom shares" in ou available to contributors that make signficant contributions over an extended period of time. These phantom shares will convert into a total of 5% of the future ou company available to selected contributors. If you make a signficant contribution towards making ou great, you can earn a share of what we believe is set to be a "Unicorn".</p>	about
