129	2021-04-21 05:28:28.886383+00	2021-04-27 22:22:21.421314+00	Important pre-launch hygiene and tweaks	<p>Currently the top bar has some things that are not yet implemented or not implemented satisfactorily for launch. Please complete the following:</p>\n<p><strong>1</strong>. "Add Product" can be retained as the label/link in the menu with a form that looks the same as the current form - but it shouldn't add a product directly. Submitting this form should create a new record/object called a CreateProductRequest which is visible via the admin console. CreateProductRequest will have the same fields as Product and should be linked to the authenticated user that created the CreateProductRequest. This functionality should only be available to authenticated users.</p>\n<p><strong>2</strong>. Hide the topbar search box for now</p>\n<p><strong>3. </strong>Remove "Commercial Partners" from the product menu list<strong> </strong></p>\n<p><strong>4. </strong>Move Ideas &amp; Bugs up to be after Product Map in the product menu</p>\n<p><strong>5</strong>. The "Find Talent" link should be removed. Please replace it with an "About" link which goes to /about.</p>\n<p>The content that displays on the about page should be editable via the admin console. For now, please put this content on the page.</p>\n<p>h1 = About ou</p>\n<p>h2 = Connecting creators everywhere.</p>\n<p>body =</p>\n<p>&lt;this video embedded (in a large size) https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OWXVryhdoVA &gt;</p>\n<p><strong>What is ou?</strong></p>\n<p>ou is the place where communities - comprising contributors of all kinds - come together to create and contribute to Open Products.</p>\n<p>The software platform that powers ou.com is itself an open product - it’s just one of the open products that you can contribute to with your skills.</p>\n<p>ou is underpinned by a simple yet powerful product management framework that greatly reduces the time required to understand what products do, and how your skills can help.</p>\n<p><strong>What's in it for me?</strong></p>\n<p>As you contribute your skills to open products at ou, you are building up a portfolio of your work - a rich portfolio where everyone can see your work and skills in action - because your work is on open products and therefore visible publicly. Your ou portfolio can help you realise the next step in your career, to avoid frustrating fake assignments in job interviews and even to potentially earn a share of new companies that are created around the Open Products that you have contributed to.</p>\n<p>The software platform that powers ou.com is itself an open product - it’s just one of the open products that you can contribute to with your skills. We plan to make "phantom shares" in ou available to contributors that make signficant contributions over an extended period of time. These phantom shares will convert into a total of 5% of the future ou company available to selected contributors. If you help make ou great, you can earn a share of what we believe is set to be a "Unicorn".</p>\n<p><strong>Why is ou needed?</strong></p>\n<p>Despite open source software being hugely successful over past decades, there have been no common ways of explaining what products do, nor the work to be done - often because open source projects are not products. They are projects that do not have a strong product management discipline, and in many cases they do not have a roadmap, they lack clearly defined goals, documentation and the work to be done is also unclear.</p>\n<p>Graphic Designers, Product Managers, Business Analysts, Finance Experts, Lawyers and others with super valuable skills, don’t write source code - so even the name “open source” suggests there are barriers to them contributing. The problems are much bigger than naming however - the terminology, practices, platforms and tools that open source projects use - such as git and Github -  are deeply technical and designed for developers only. Ever heard of a graphic designer doing a “git pull request”?</p>\n<p>For many people who can code, becoming a contributor is also intimidating - often there isn’t an efficient or effective way of figuring out where to start, finding specific work to contribute or even how to interact with other contributors on that project.</p>\n<p><strong>Who are the founders and investors?</strong></p>\n<p>Adrian McPhee  &lt;linked in brand icon with link... https://www.linkedin.com/in/adrianmcphee/ (target="_blank" please)&gt; &lt;twitter brand icon with link... https://twitter.com/adrianmcphee&gt;</p>\n<p>Farbod Saraf &lt;linked in brand icon with link...  https://www.linkedin.com/in/farbodsaraf/ (target="_blank" please)&gt; &lt;twitter brand icon with link... https://twitter.com/farbodsaraf&gt;</p>\n<p>To date, we have designed/built and funded ou ourselves. We are now using the product to manage itself and we need your help to make ou a success. Please find a task that matches your skills, claim it and get started!</p>\n<p>As above, we plan to make "phantom shares" in ou available to contributors that make signficant contributions over an extended period of time. These phantom shares will convert into a total of 5% of the future ou company available to selected contributors. If you make a signficant contribution towards making ou great, you can earn a share of what we believe is set to be a "Unicorn".</p>\n	4	8d5c116e-fbdd-4065-af07-e08abca21563	\N	801327ef-e7b7-48fb-823d-bce8d0d700e3	fffe07ad-beaa-4bc4-b621-2e7537b707b5	Add about page. Create CreateProductRequest model and connect to "Add Product" form in authenticated manner. Remove "Find Talent" and search from top bar.	f	f	\N	0	43	t	71	8d5c116e-fbdd-4065-af07-e08abca21563	3	\N	\N
