125	2021-04-18 21:00:33.803224+00	2021-04-25 14:38:58.816776+00	Admin or manager should be able to approve or reject tasks	<p>Users contribution needs to be reviewed by admins or managers and they can either approve or reject the contribution.</p>\n<p>When the users submit a claimed task for review, the status should be changed and in the UI for the task detail view and task list, instead of "Claimed", "In Review" should appear and the username of the Reviewer should appear next to the status (similar to the way that we show the user profile of the user who claimed the task next to the "Claimed" status when it's claimed).</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Design</strong></p>\n<p>For the tasks that are submitted for review, there needs to be two blue buttons appear in the task detail page under the delete and edit task button, the top one should has a lable of "Approve the work", and the below one should be "Reject the work". The design / style of the button should be similar to claim the task button which contributors see.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The flow is as below:</p>\n<p></p>\n<img src="/images/attachments/2021-04-18 20:44:24 20af7832.png" alt="undefined" style="height: auto;width: 100%"/>\n<p></p>\n<p>The data model should change as follow:</p>\n<img src="/images/attachments/2021-04-18 20:43:08 fccbcc69.png" alt="undefined" style="height: auto;width: 100%"/>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>When the task gets completed:</strong></p>\n<p>In the UI the task will have a status "Completed" with the user profile of the person who completes the tasks in both task detail page and task list page. The task will be added to the user profile of the contributor as well.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Acceptance Criteria:</strong></p>\n<p>As a user, admin or manager, when a task is submitted for review, I see the status "In Review" on the task on both task detail page and task list pages with the user profile of the Reviewer in front of the task.</p>\n<p>As an admin or manager, when a task is submitted for review, I see two buttons to approve or reject work in the task detail page under the edit and delete button (top right of the page).</p>\n<p>As an admin or manager, when I approve a work, the task will be marked as Completed in the UI with the user profile of the person who completed it and still will be part of the tasks in the Task detail page.</p>\n<p><span style="color: rgba(0,0,0,0.85);background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-size: 14px;font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, "Noto Sans", sans-serif, "Apple Color Emoji", "Segoe UI Emoji", "Segoe UI Symbol", "Noto Color Emoji;">As an admin or manager, when I reject a work, the task should become available again for claim.</span></p>\n<p>As a contributor, when my submitted work gets approved, the task will be added to my portfolio.</p>\n	3	801327ef-e7b7-48fb-823d-bce8d0d700e3	3	801327ef-e7b7-48fb-823d-bce8d0d700e3	226f7457-0639-4d48-8328-b27f3d1a871a	Users contribution needs to be reviewed by admins or managers and they can either approve or reject the contribution.	f	f	126	0	41	t	69	801327ef-e7b7-48fb-823d-bce8d0d700e3	3	\N	\N
