137	2021-05-24 13:19:39.027714+00	2021-06-09 08:34:12.382215+00	Custom User model and related improvements	<p>1. Implement custom user model <a href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/3.2/topics/auth/customizing/#specifying-custom-user-model" target="_blank">https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/3.2/topics/auth/customizing/#specifying-custom-user-model</a> and remove our "Username" and "Authorised User" models.</p>\n<p>2. <span style="color: rgb(34,34,34);background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-size: small;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">PERSON_TYPE enum</span> should not be shared by <span style="color: rgb(34,34,34);background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-size: small;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">OrganisationPerson and </span>ProductPerson.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Requirements:&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="color: rgb(34,34,34);background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-size: small;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Usernames are unique</span></li>\n<li style="text-align:start;"><span style="color: rgb(34,34,34);background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-size: small;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Organisations and People both have Usernames</span></li>\n<li style="text-align:start;"><span style="color: rgb(34,34,34);background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-size: small;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Given the above, if the username "acme" is taken by a company, a user cannot claim that username and vice versa</span></li>\n<li style="text-align:start;"><span style="color: rgb(34,34,34);background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-size: small;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">There are a number of reserved words that are not acceptable usernames (can start with the list below)</span></li>\n<li style="text-align:start;"><span style="color: rgb(34,34,34);background-color: rgb(255,255,255);font-size: small;font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Users can be super users (as per standard django) and this is required to