136	2021-05-24 13:15:08.966196+00	2021-06-09 09:10:29.765465+00	Completely remove "stacks" and add Task Categories and related Expertise	<p>Please see this list of Task Categories and related Expertise: <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1f7aDyfBEcg3N3UWx7xc-jHX9I3owpRBnFgiJoNzIuII/edit?usp=sharing" target="_self">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1f7aDyfBEcg3N3UWx7xc-jHX9I3owpRBnFgiJoNzIuII/edit?usp=sharing</a></p>\n<p>Note that the Expertise is a multi dimensional template for tags that are scoped to each Task Category. When copied onto a user's profile or task, the hierarchy can be represented as for example:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Backend Development</li>\n<ul>\n<li>Python Ecosystem</li>\n<ul>\n<li>Django</li>\n</ul>\n<li>Languages</li>\n<ul>\n<li>Java, Python, Golang</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p>Only "active" rows will be visible/used in OU at launch and only "selectable" Task Categories may be selected. Active, non selectable Task Categories are for navigation in the tree select. For each active, selectable row in the spreadsheet we should have Expertise specified as required. Expertise (tags) will be copied/stored on Task and TaskListing, but the values can only come from the Expertise field in Task Category which acts as an two dimensional Expertise/tag template for Tasks.</p>\n<p>Due to iterations/changes we currently have "stacks" in multiple places in the data model, "required skills" in the UI and other tags in places I think, and it's not clean/deliberate enough.</p>\n<p>Therefore I think we should:</p>\n<p>0. Implement TaskCategory and the Expertise as per the <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1f7aDyfBEcg3N3UWx7xc-jHX9I3owpRBnFgiJoNzIuII/edit?usp=sharing" target="_self">google spreadsheet </a> - via the admin console, we need to be able to quickly activate categories and add Expertise etc.</p>\n<p>1. Require Tasks to have one Task Category, which is specified in the task creation process. (the list from the google sheet - Ant Tree Select can be used for selecting this https://ant.design/components/tree-select/)</p>\n<p>2. In Task authoring, allow multiple Expertise (tags) to be selected that relate to the selected Task Category. The Task should have a task_category_id and multiple Expertise items/tags.</p>\n<p>3. Update TaskListing accordingly. For context, please see <a href="https://ou.com/meta/ou-product-factory/tasks/18" target="_self">https://ou.com/meta/ou-product-factory/tasks/18</a></p>\n<p>4. Allow profiles to have up to five Task Categories and up to three related Expertise tags for each Category</p>\n<p>5. Allow filtering of Tasks by Task Category, and also by Expertise</p>\n<p>6. Initiatives can also be tagged (loose, up to three tags - no preset or restricted tags, note: this is not Expertise just user-defined tags)</p>\n<p>7. Products can also be tagged (loose, up to three tags - no preset or restricted tags, note: this is not Expertise just user-defined tags)</p>\n<p>8. Remove "stacks" everywhere.</p>\n	2	8d5c116e-fbdd-4065-af07-e08abca21563	4	8d5c116e-fbdd-4065-af07-e08abca21563	a80a3075-c7a6-4961-9423-bfebf5af4a40	Currently we have "stacks" in several places in data model and "Required Skills" in the UI, we need to be more deliberate	f	f	\N	0	48	t	101	8d5c116e-fbdd-4065-af07-e08abca21563	3		\N
146	2021-05-31 01:03:02.488723+00	2021-06-09 16:50:29.544874+00	Implement Delivery Message capability	<p>Once a contributor tries to submit a Task for review, they should be prompt with a window to provide more context on the work they have done. This prompt should be a modal which allows them to provide a short message and attach files if needed. The message would help them to provide more context to the reviewer and the attachment capability would help them to attach files, such as PDF, Word file, image, Figma export, etc..</p>\n<p>Regarding the data model, my (@adrian) suggestion is to add a model TaskDeliveryAttempt which belongs to TaskClaim: one TaskClaim may have one or many related TaskDeliveryAttempt objects, TaskDeliveryAttempt will have a foreign key of "task_claim_id" or similar. TaskDeliveryAttempt should have a status of either: New, Accepted, Rejected - Try Again, Rejected - TaskClaim Cancelled. If there is one TaskDeliveryAttempt with a status of "Accepted", then the related TaskClaim is complete and there can be no further TaskDeliveryAttempts for that TaskClaim.</p>\n<p>Some elaboration on TaskDeliveryAttempt statuses: "New" means that the TaskDeliveryAttempt has been created by the TaskClaim's contributor and the Task reviewer needs to review it. A TaskDeliveryAttempt status of  "Accepted" means delivery was accepted by the reviewer. There are two types of "Rejected": 1. Reject delivery but allow another delivery attempt by contributor  or 2. Reject delivery and make Task available to other contributors. If the latter (2), then the related TaskClaim should be cancelled and the Task (and TaskListing) return to available status. The contributor should receive a clear notification via email in each of the three scenarios (accepted, rejected - try again, rejected - task claim cancelled). Once the status of "rejected - task claim cancelled" is saved, it is not possible to undo/revert. So, there should be a confimation message to the reviewer about this.</p>\n<p>The character limit for the message in the TaskDeliveryAttempt should be 255 characters. We should reuse the same text box for Short Description that we already have in the task creation modal since it has the same charachter limit and stops users if it goes beyond the limit.</p>\n<p>The design of the modal should be as below:</p>\n<p><img src="/images/attachments/2021-05-31 00:33:37 d3aed8d3.png" alt="undefined" style="height: undefined;width: undefined"/></p>\n<p>For the attachment section design and implementation, please reuse the attachment sectoin that we already have in the capability creation modal. We already have the exact same design. Currently it only accept URLs but it should also accept uploading into S3. It has been once implemented before so I'm not sure why it's not currently reflected in the attachment of the capability creation modal.</p>\n<p>Once the attachments are added, the design looks like this: (identical to capability creation modal)</p>\n<p><img src="/images/attachments/2021-05-31 00:36:33 9e18b6a7.png" alt="undefined" style="height: undefined;width: undefined"/></p>\n<p>The delivery message is optional so contributors can simply press on Submit without entering any message or uploading/adding any attachments.</p>\n<p>Once the work is submitted for the review, if delivery message is not left empty (e.g. if there's a delivery message entered or an delivery attachment has been added), then a small text appears after the sentence "The task is submitted for the review." which says "See Delivery Message" and the Delivery Message is hyperlink where a reviewer can click to open the modal that includes the Delivery Message and Attachment. The design is as follows:</p>\n<p><img src="/images/attachments/2021-05-31 00:47:56 39e639d9.png" alt="undefined" style="height: undefined;width: undefined"/></p>\n<p>If the reviewer clicks on Delivery Message in the screen above, then a modal will be shown as below:</p>\n<p><img src="/images/attachments/2021-05-31 00:58:46 0965d064.png" alt="undefined" style="height: undefined;width: undefined"/></p>\n<p>Here is the Figma file to the design:</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.figma.com/file/rZQCEDfmV55LFg76dB8Ysr/o-u-(Copy)?node-id=219%3A868" target="_self">https://www.figma.com/file/rZQCEDfmV55LFg76dB8Ysr/o-u-(Copy)?node-id=219%3A868</a></p>\n<p>Please aim for resuse as much as possible + use the ant design to achieve 100% consistency with the designs above.</p>\n	3	801327ef-e7b7-48fb-823d-bce8d0d700e3	4	8d5c116e-fbdd-4065-af07-e08abca21563	8f1ee6a8-6528-40a6-bf7f-284a834d1b52	Contributors should be prompted to provide a delivery message when they submit their work for review. Core teams should be able to read the delivery message while reviewing a submitted work.	f	f	948	0	55	t	106	801327ef-e7b7-48fb-823d-bce8d0d700e3	3		\N
147	2021-05-31 01:13:11.750034+00	2021-05-31 01:13:11.822818+00	Allow image upload through pasting or drag and drop	<p>Currently attaching an image to the task description can be done only through wysiwyg image uploaded. It should be possible to simply add image to the description by pasting an image from the clipboard (e.g. using command+V) or drag and dropping an image into the description. This speeds up the task creation especially for tasks that have multiple images.</p>\n	2	801327ef-e7b7-48fb-823d-bce8d0d700e3	14	801327ef-e7b7-48fb-823d-bce8d0d700e3	cde58c7a-d436-40a6-bde2-143d35947a40	Currently attaching an image to the task description can be done only through wysiwyg image uploaded. It should be possible to simply add image to the description by pasting or drag and dropping an image into the description	f	f	115	2	56	t	\N	801327ef-e7b7-48fb-823d-bce8d0d700e3	3		\N
