23	Show the currently claimed task by a contributor who tries to claim a new task	<p>Contributors should not be able to claim a new task if they already have an uncompleted claimed task on the same product. This is to avoid contributors claiming multiple tasks at the same time and slowing down the progress on each and yet blocking other contributors from claiming them. Currently if a contributor tries to claim a new task, they receive an error message saying that they cannot claim a new task as they already have a claimed task, but it doesn't show which task is currently claimed by them which leads to a confusion if a developer cannot recall what they previously claimed. It would be great to include a mention of the task they already claimed as an hyperlink which links to that task. The error message should be:</p>\n<p>"You already have a claimed task which needs to be completed before you will be able to claim a new task on this product: [Name of the task which is a hyperlink to the task page]"</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>While implementing this task, please check if the restriction on the task claim is properly implemented per product. So if a contributor has a claimed task on one product, they should be able to claim another task on another product in parallel so the restriction is only per product. This is because if a contributor gets blocked on a task for any reason e.g. their task is currently being reviewed by the core team, they should not be blocked from contributing to other products.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Test cases:</strong></p>\n<p>As a contributor who already has a claimed task on a product (doesn't matter if it's already in review or not), when I try to claim a new task in the same product, I should receive an error which contains a link to the currently claimed task on this product.</p>\n<p>As a contributor who claimed a task on one product, I should be able to claim a task on another product and work on them in parallel.</p>	Contributors who alread