75	Implement new UI for Inactive screen	<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Task description</span></h2>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">On this screen Admin would be able to see the list of de-activated users and have access to reviewing those users&rsquo; details and managing their records</span></p>\r\n<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Interactive prototype</span></h2>\r\n<p><a href="https://projects.invisionapp.com/share/VSTQ2MSMHTE#/screens/385217264"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://projects.invisionapp.com/share/VSTQ2MSMHTE#/screens/385217264</span></a></p>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">User is able to view the Active Users list, including</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Username</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">User can go to a user details screen by clicking on the username in the list</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Display Name</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Deactivated from</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">if &ldquo;Deactivated from&rdquo; time is less than 1 hour the time should be displayed time in minutes (rounded)</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">if &ldquo;Deactivated from&rdquo; time is between 1 hour and 1 day time should be displayed in hours (rounded)</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">if &ldquo;Deactivated from&rdquo; time is between 1 day and 7 days, time should be displayed in days (rounded)</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">if &ldquo;Deactivated from&rdquo; is more than 7 days, time should be displayed in weeks (rounded)</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Auth method can be</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">"2FA" if 2-factor authentication is enabled</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">SFA if 2-factor authentication is disabled</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Groups</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Groups tab should be displaying all the groups this member is a part of</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">User has the following quick actions which can be applied to each of the user records in the list:</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Edit</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Takes to the user profile page which can be edited&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Change password</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Leads to Change Password screen for a selected user</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Consents and Data transfer</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Takes to the Consents and Data Transfer screen for a selected user</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Activate users</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Moves user to the active users list</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">&nbsp;Delete&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Allows to delete user from the system whatsoever</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">User is able to filter Active users by Group (Design:</span><a href="https://projects.invisionapp.com/share/VSTQ2MSMHTE#/screens/382949533"> <span style="font-weight: 400;">https://projects.invisionapp.com/share/VSTQ2MSMHTE#/screens/382949533</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">)</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">User has "Only Admins" and "Only Locked" filters always visible</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">User can select one or more groups to filter active users by</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once a filter is enabled, user can clear the selection or remove each individual filter</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Mass selection and actions</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Designs:</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://projects.invisionapp.com/share/TVU4L22NQR5#/screens"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://projects.invisionapp.com/share/VSTQ2MSMHTE#/screens/382949533</span></a></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://projects.invisionapp.com/share/UAU4L2BVYT6#/screens"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://projects.invisionapp.com/share/UAU4L2BVYT6#/screens</span></a></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">https://projects.invisionapp.com/share/GUU4L2X6ENK#/screens</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">User can select single or multiple entry via a checkbox</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">User has then mass deactivate and mass delete entries from the list</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">If &ldquo;Delete&rdquo; option is selected confirmation prompt should show up</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Copy:</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">For Single user deletion: &ldquo;Are you sure want to remove all information related to &lt;username&gt; in AuthMachine and all relying parties? This action can not be undone&rdquo;</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">For multiple users: &ldquo;Are you sure want to remove all information related to &lt;users_selected_count&gt; in AuthMachine and all relying parties? This action can not be undone&rdquo;</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">User should be able to search by:</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Username</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Display name (essentialy first name and last name)</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sorting should be available for these fields:</span></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Username: Alphabetical (A-&gt;Z and Z-&gt;A)</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Display name: (A-&gt;Z and Z-&gt;A)</span></li>\r\n<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Last login: Most Recent and Least Recent</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>	On this screen Admin would be able to see the list of de-activated users and have access to reviewing those users&rsquo; details and managing their records	1	{Django,Postgresql,new-tag,hbh}	f	f	0	5	t	{"username": "matthew-haddad", "full_name": "Mat (Admin of Hectic and PM at AM))"}	{"username": "igor", "full_name": "Igor (Admin of AM)"}	{"username": "john-smith", "full_name": "Farbod (Admin of OU & Contributor of AM)"}	1	\N	\N	t	1	\N	24	c748aeb0-9459-475d-a8c3-fdd54ccc