112	Completely remove "stacks" and add Task Categories and related Expertise	<p>Please see this list of Task Categories and related Expertise: <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1f7aDyfBEcg3N3UWx7xc-jHX9I3owpRBnFgiJoNzIuII/edit?usp=sharing" target="_self">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1f7aDyfBEcg3N3UWx7xc-jHX9I3owpRBnFgiJoNzIuII/edit?usp=sharing</a></p>\n<p>Note that the Expertise is a multi dimensional template for tags that are scoped to each Task Category. When copied onto a user's profile or task, the hierarchy can be represented as for example:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Backend Development</li>\n<ul>\n<li>Python Ecosystem</li>\n<ul>\n<li>Django</li>\n</ul>\n<li>Languages</li>\n<ul>\n<li>Java, Python, Golang</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p>Only "active" rows will be visible/used in OU at launch and only "selectable" Task Categories may be selected. Active, non selectable Task Categories are for navigation in the tree select. For each active, selectable row in the spreadsheet we should have Expertise specified as required. Expertise (tags) will be copied/stored on Task and TaskListing, but the values can only come from the Expertise field in Task Category which acts as an two dimensional Expertise/tag template for Tasks.</p>\n<p>Due to iterations/changes we currently have "stacks" in multiple places in the data model, "required skills" in the UI and other tags in places I think, and it's not clean/deliberate enough.</p>\n<p>Therefore I think we should:</p>\n<p>0. Implement TaskCategory and the Expertise as per the <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1f7aDyfBEcg3N3UWx7xc-jHX9I3owpRBnFgiJoNzIuII/edit?usp=sharing" target="_self">google spreadsheet </a> - via the admin console, we need to be able to quickly activate categories and add Expertise etc.</p>\n<p>1. Require Tasks to have one Task Category, which is specified in the task creation process. (the list from the google sheet - Ant Tree Select can be used for selecting this https://ant.design